[build] Use system unzip for NDK on Unix

bsdtar's `.zip` reader on macOS does not preserve symlinks - it silently
materializes them as zero-byte files. The NDK contains many such symlinks
(`clang++ -> clang`, `x86_64-linux-android24-clang -> clang`, ld variants,
etc), so the empty placeholders then fail with `posix_spawn: Exec format
error` when clang tries to invoke them as the linker.

Add a per-item `UseUnzipOnUnix=true` opt-in plus an `UnzipSubdir=...` hint,
and in `_ExtractAndroidSdkPackages` route those items through:

    unzip -q -o ZIP -d PARENT_OF_DEST
    rmdir DEST && mv PARENT_OF_DEST/UnzipSubdir DEST

System `unzip` preserves symlinks correctly. Everything else continues to
use `tar -xf` (works fine; no symlinks). Windows still uses `tar` for the
NDK too because the Windows NDK zip is `.exe`-only.

